HEADWORD: Saxophone
<hw>Sax"o*phone</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[A.A.J.
<ets>Sax</ets>, the inventor (see <er>Saxhorn</er>) + Gr. <?/
tone.]</ety> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>A wind instrument of brass,
containing a reed, and partaking of the qualities both of a brass
instrument and of a clarinet.</def>⟦br⟧
